# Project 4: Reader of Books

* Author: Chloe Johnson
* Class: CS121 Section 2
* Semester: Spring 2019

## Overview

This Java application displays a GUI with a reader panel, a library panel, and 
a reader of books panel. Books are loaded into a library and the user can
select a book to read. 

## Compiling and Using

To compile, execute the following command in the main project directory:
```
$ javac ReaderOfBooks.java
```

Run the compiled class with the command:
```
$ java ReaderOfBooks
```

The application will open a window that allows the user to load books into the library 
and read them.
## Sources used

- I found code for creating borders on docs.oracle.com.
https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/components/border.html

- I found code for removing borders on stackoverflow.com
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26855468/remove-border-from-jscrollpane?rq=1

- I found code for removing all components from a panel on stackoverflow.com
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/38349445/how-to-delete-all-components-in-a-jpanel-dynamically?rq=1

